This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with routing protocols in Mobile Ad hoc Networks (MANETs). It also involves game theory, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with decision-making in strategic situations, making cs.GT another likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization, which could place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a mechanism to ensure proper cooperation in routing, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
